		{
			"id":"f729d8e72451ab0a",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# SIUE Plan\n\n## Plan (2026-07-04)\n\nBy the time I transfer to SIUE, I will have finished up to:\n- Differential Equations\n- Physics 3\n- Statics, Dynamics, and Mechanics of Solids\n- Macroeconomics\n- Computer Programming for Engineers\n\nI'm hoping to test out of CS 150 Intro to Computing II, so that I can fill the prerequisite for CS482 Computer Graphics. The main problem in this case, is that I need to take CS 286 Intro to Computer Organization and I can only take one non-ECE course elective. I would have to pay this one out of pocket, if Financial Aid doesn't cover it. Hopefully by then, I might be able to figure something out with scholarship.\n\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-1500,
			"y":720,
			"width":720,
			"height":780
		}
	],
